#: paragraph:16,sentence:1
msgctxt ""
"Notice there’s not a word about carefully learning anything, only daily "
"practicing in the face of one’s disbelief. And practice Bill did, but what "
"was he practicing? The last section of the text, “Choose Once Again,” was "
"one of his favorites and he took it to heart. “Trials are but lessons that "
"you failed to learn presented once again, so where you made a faulty choice "
"before you now can make a better one, and thus escape all pain that what you"
" chose before has brought to you.”[8] He was determined to notice the times "
"when he lost his peace—times that threatened his self-image or when things "
"weren’t unfolding as he thought they should. As swiftly as possible he would"
" choose to let them go, realizing he was the author of his own distress. One"
" can almost see his original mind-set being released and these new, yet "
"timeless, values being adopted."
msgid ""
"Notice there’s not a word about carefully learning anything, only daily "
"practicing in the face of one’s disbelief."
msgstr ""

