"Helen, “I was quite uncomfortable with Helen, or I should say slightly "
"terrified, because I didn’t know which social skills to use with her. She "
"was an anomaly to me. You didn’t know if you were getting through. You "
"didn’t know whether you should be open, closed, chatty, quiet—at least I "
"didn’t know. But with Bill I was so relaxed because I felt so comfortable "
"with him.”[15]"
